author: Jorge Alonso
title: Vanderbilt’s Matthew Fisher-Davis Has A Brain Fart And Commits Intentional Foul That Cost His Team The Game At NCAA Tourney
text:
Vanderbilt’s Matthe Fisher-Davis probably wants to get away right now. 
During today’s Vanderbilt-Northwestern game, Fisher-Davis inexplicably committed an intentional foul to put Northwestern on the free throw line with 15 seconds left in the game despite his team being up. 
Thanks to Fisher-Davis’ foul, Northwestern was able to go up and they never looked back. How unfortunate.
